Description: Livrada offers an e-book card which is a physical gift card, allowing the holder to redeem and download e-books onto their e-reader devices.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Making e-book gifting personal Livrada was founded to make e-book gifting more personal. For centuries, people have given books to each other. Books are the perfect gift; meaningful and personal, a book reflects the thought that the gift-giver put into the purchase. We created Livrada title-based e-book gift cards (US Patent pending) to recapture this experience. We want to reintroduce a personal touch into the world of digital media, starting with e-books. What is a Livrada e-book card? A Livrada e-book card is a (physical) gift card, sold at retail, that represents a specific e-book title (e.g., The Adventures of Tom Sawyer ). Each card is beautifully designed with the book cover art and also includes a description, much like a traditional book jacket. The card allows the holder to redeem and download the specific e-book onto their e-reader device. At launch, this includes all Kindle and NOOK devices. The plan is to expand to other e-readers soon. The Company Livrada, Inc., based in Southern California, was formed in January 2012 by an experienced team of entrepreneurs with deep business and technology backgrounds. Our team consists of experienced executives from the digital media, wireless, pre-paid, payments, and e-commerce industries. We’ve spent time at world-class companies like Virgin Mobile USA, Warner Music Group, McKinsey & Co., Deloitte, and Lexis-Nexis, as well as a number of scrappy start-ups. We are lovers of technology who happen to believe that the off-line “real world” offers experiences that cannot be replicated in digital. We think Livrada e-book gift cards are a great way to start.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Consumer Electronics, Financial Services, Hardware, Software

SemantX solves the major impediment to the exchange of medical records.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: SemantX solves the major impediment to the exchange of medical records:  Easy-to-use, affordable,  universal, interoperability for electronic medical records.  Various infrastructures already exist to electronically send medical records between disparate healthcare providers such as the widespread use of the DIRECT protocol.  But, because of the thousands of different existing data formats and complex semantics, a medical record sent by one provider cannot be understood or consumed by the receiving provider's system. The SemantX SaaS service provides a complete, affordable solution to the problem of Health information interoperability.   With a simple software download, Healthcare Providers can be up and exchanging medical records in hours, not days or weeks.  Their self-contained solution does not require any sophisticated IT resources. It's priced at a low-cost subscription and it is designed to significantly reduce maintenance costs.  What this means -- even the smallest Healthcare Provider can now afford electronic healthcare interoperability. The solution is based on MDMI, a published message interoperability standard that is supported by healthcare standards bodies. As soon as a Provider joins the service, the Provider will be able to send validated messages to Federal and State agencies in the required complex message standards.  But they will not need to know those standards or keep track of any changes in those standards.

Description: Centric App is a video discovery & sharing platform that matches video content from social platforms with local audiences.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Centric App is a video discovery and sharing platform that matches video content from social platforms with local audiences. Problem: There is no user friendly, free, public facing platform that aggregates videos by location from social media. (e.g. YouTube, Twitter, Periscope). Centric App allows users to organically discover videos of what’s happening around them and see what’s going on outside the “echo chamber” - of their own networks. At the same time creators need a way to connect organically and share video content with audiences that does not involve infiltrating their social networks or gaming social platforms algorithms. The result is a dis-connect, with users missing out on what’s happening around them and creators producing huge amounts of content that is not reaching new viewers, growing audiences or monetizing. In reality it is gathering dust. Solution: Centric App allows anyone to quickly discover videos being published around them, whatever the channel or platform. They can find out what’s happening locally, discover new content, share and comment. They can follow, engage and connect with creators and publishers on the source platform. Bottom line is Centric matches video content by location, just like Tinder, bringing audiences and videos together. Centric shares undiscovered content with a new audience and grows reach for content producers. ￼

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Konviv is a mobile fintech startup using an artificially intelligent chatbot to engage consumers in building better financial behavior. As users engage with the platform, Konviv uses machine learning to provide customized financial guidance through smart notifications, in turn Konviv builds a financial health score for each user – using data that truly captures the way each individual manages their money. As their score increases, users are able to access new services and increased access to capital on the platform. Konviv comes from the Spanish word: convivir. Convivir is a beautiful, poetic, and lively word. It literally means to coexist or to exist side by side with something. Konviv is an acknowledgement that finances are an undeniable part of our social fabric. With every financial transaction there is a human exchange. Konviv strives to make each financial exchange more touching, more empowering, and more impactful. Konviv – more than a financial app – is a movement.
